Maps a unit error into the supplied application error value.
Signature Check.orError&#32;error&#32;result Parameters Name Type Description error &lsquo;error The domain error of type 'error to return on failure. result Check&lt;&lsquo;value&gt; The source Check. Returns Type Description Result&lt;&lsquo;value, &rsquo;error&gt; A Result with the provided error value. Remarks This is the primary bridge from checks to domain-specific results.
Examples &quot;&quot; |&gt; Check.okIfNonEmptyStr |&gt; Check.orError &quot;Empty string&quot; // Error &quot;Empty string&quot; &quot;hello&quot; |&gt; Check.okIfNonEmptyStr |&gt; Check.orError &quot;Empty string&quot; // Ok &quot;hello&quot;
